post.summary: This endpoint retrieves Cafeteria Ratings from the Backend.

parameters.name: eventId
parameters.description: optional parameter, will return all events if no id is specified

get.summary: a location is a campus location/building, e.g. "Garching Forschungszentrum"

cafeteriaId.title: cafeteriaId Mandatory Name of the cafeteria (EAT-API naming scheme "MENSA_GARCHING")

from.title: Optional Parameter to define an interval for the ratings (Lower bound)

to.title: Optional Parameter to define an interval for the ratings (Upper bound)

limit.title: Optional Parameter defines how many ratings are queried. If all ratings should be queried, enter "-1"

from.title: Optional Parameter to define an interval for the ratings (Lower bound)

to.title: Optional Parameter to define an interval for the ratings (Upper bound)

count.description: The absolut count of humans in the canteen or 0 in case no data is available.

maxCount.description: The maximum nunmber of humans in the canteen for the percent to be 100.00 or 0 in case no data is available.

percent.description: Current capacity utilization of the canteen or -1 in case no data is available.

timestamp.description: A time stamp indicating how up to date the response is or an unspecified value in case there is no data available (precent == -1).

ratingTags.title: Optional list of tag ratings add as many tags with a rating (1-5) of the list of cafeteriaRatingTags
